64,IssuesEvent,2015-10-03 14:50:40+00:00,27924304,cdent/gabbi,3515,FND,,,opened,support for form data,[],[],0,"Testing HTML forms currently requires manually encoding the submitted data:

```yaml
- name: create new item
  POST: /items
  request_headers:
      Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded
  data: name=foo
```

This gets unwieldy as soon as there are multiple parameters and/or the data requires encoding:

```yaml
  data: name=hello%20world&desc=l%C3%B6r%C3%A4m%20ips%C3%BCm&tag=foo&tag=bar&...
```

(that's still a fairly tame example)

This greatly impedes readability. It also seems inconsistent, given the support for structured data in `query_parameters` and JSON request bodies (the docs specifically mention this allows ""more flexibility when doing a `POST` or `PUT` - there's no reason this affordance should be limited to JSON).

Since form submissions - or, more generally, `application/x-www-form-urlencoded` - is fairly common, even beyond browser-based applications (i.e. APIs), gabbi should auto-encode form data (as determined by the `Content-Type` header):

```yaml
  data:
      name: hello world
      desc: löräm ipsüm
      tag: [foo, bar]
```

(Arguably we might also want to support an ordered sequence of key-value pairs.)
",{},{}
