566,IssuesEvent,2018-02-27 17:24:01+00:00,28530868,cannatag/ldap3,8628770,CnlPepper,,,opened,No equivalent to escape_dn_chars to escape dn strings.,[],[],0,"Until recently I've been using the python-ldap package but have just started moving to ldap3 as it has a cleaner API and fewer dependencies. There is one function I can't seem to find. To prevent injections into dn strings when e.g. using bind and taking in a username, the username needs to be escaped to prevent users injecting data into the dn string e.g. if they supply ""blah,abc=123"" it would result in a modified dn string.

In python-ldap there is the escape_dn_chars function (see https://github.com/python-ldap/python-ldap/blob/master/Lib/ldap/dn.py), I feel this should be available in the ldap3.utils.dn module. I've found the equivalent filter escape function, but it does not cover all the characters that must be handled for a dn according to RFC 4514.

For now I've reimplemented the function locally, could this be added to the package it no equivalent exists?",{},{}
