907,IssuesEvent,2017-06-02 02:26:56+00:00,53603584,niklasf/fishnet,14872,apetresc,,,opened,"Provide way to do a ""clean"" shutdown",[],[],0,"At the moment, as far as I know, the only way to exit fishnet is to send it a SIGINT, usually with Ctrl-c. So if I don't want to cancel an analysis in progress, I have to watch and wait for the move counter to go to 0 and hope there isn't another one queued up.

