2532,IssuesEvent,2015-09-11 12:35:14+00:00,30379674,adamchainz/django-mysql,857609,adamchainz,,,opened,FoundRowsPaginator,[],[],0,"Using `sql_calc_found_rows` from #115 , a paginator could be built that uses a single select query rather than one to generate the count and another to get the data. This can often, but not always, be faster - see [this percona blogpost](https://www.percona.com/blog/2007/08/28/to-sql_calc_found_rows-or-not-to-sql_calc_found_rows/).

N.B. I started on this during implementation in #150 , but dropped the paginator since it was getting too complex and would probably require some features dropping, like `orphans`. The code still sits here on a branch at https://github.com/adamchainz/django-mysql/tree/found_rows_paginator",{},{}
