2770,IssuesEvent,2017-06-02 13:08:44+00:00,46218363,nnseva/django-jsoneditor,496812,nnseva,,,closed,js 404 (Not Found),[],[],5,"Hi, i was getting `http://localhost:8000/static/django-jsoneditor/django-jsoneditor.js 404 (Not Found)` and i got it working by copying the `js` here in the repository to my own static folder.

I am using Postgres built in JsonField mentioned here https://github.com/nnseva/django-jsoneditor/issues/16 and things seem to be working fine (after i fix the not found issue). I tested with `django-jsonfield` and everything works fine there.

I have my `forms.py`

```python
from jsoneditor.forms import JSONEditor

class Model1Form(forms.ModelForm):

    class Meta:
        model = Model1
        fields = '__all__'
        widgets = {
            'answer_data': JSONEditor()
        }
```

and then in `admin.py` i just plug the `form=Model1Form`. I find this approach to be `less dirty` like mentioned [here](https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/1.10/ref/contrib/admin/#django.contrib.admin.ModelAdmin.formfield_overrides)

