3041,IssuesEvent,2015-03-30 07:13:48+00:00,31664927,martinpitt/python-dbusmock,200109,martinpitt,,,closed,All dbus.exceptions.DBusExceptions are instansiated incorrectly,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/martinpitt/python-dbusmock/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}]",[],1,"It seems `dbus.exceptions.DBusException` takes a `name` keyword argument per [1]. This means that

    raise dbus.exceptions.DBusException('org.bluez.Error.NoSuchAdapter',
        'No such adapter.')

will raise an exception that is not named `org.bluez.Error.NoSuchAdapter`, but rather named `org.freedesktop.DBus.Python.dbus.exceptions.DBusException`. Code expecting specific exceptions will thus not work as expected.

[1] http://dbus.freedesktop.org/doc/dbus-python/api/dbus.exceptions.DBusException-class.html",{},{}
