3594,IssuesEvent,2018-06-12 08:12:51+00:00,34864402,apache/incubator-mxnet,5899962,dwSun,47359,apache,opened,weird gpu memory usage,[],[],0,"## Description
The script below will eat all gpu memory gradually in the first epoch. Sometimes it will cause OOM error and crash.
Sometimes it just keep running, but at the 2rd epoch, the gpu memory and cuda core usage will drop to a very low level suddenly.

## Environment info (Required)
ubuntu 18.04 cuda91
nvidia driver 390.48
nvidia 1080ti gpu card

mxnet-cu91 1.2.0 from pypi (with or without mkl)

## Minimum reproducible example
```py
#!/usr/bin/env python3
import time
from multiprocessing import cpu_count

import mxnet as mx
from mxnet import autograd, gluon
from mxnet.gluon.data import dataset
from mxnet.gluon.data.vision import transforms
from mxnet.gluon.model_zoo import vision

CPU_COUNT = cpu_count()
mx.random.seed(42)  # set seed for repeatability

class ImgDataSet(dataset.Dataset):
    def __getitem__(self, idx):
        return mx.nd.random.uniform(shape=(320, 320, 3)), 0

    def __len__(self):
        return 50000

transformer = transforms.Compose([
    transforms.Resize(224),
    transforms.ToTensor()])


train_dataset = ImgDataSet()
train_dataset = train_dataset.transform_first(transformer)

batch_size = 16
train_data_loader = mx.gluon.data.DataLoader(
    train_dataset, batch_size, shuffle=True, num_workers=CPU_COUNT)

# construct and initialize network.
ctx = mx.gpu() if mx.test_utils.list_gpus() else mx.cpu()

net = vision.get_mobilenet_v2(1.0, ctx=ctx, classes=1000)
net.hybridize()
net.initialize(mx.init.Xavier(factor_type='out'), ctx=ctx)
# define loss and trainer.
criterion = gluon.loss.SoftmaxCrossEntropyLoss()
trainer = gluon.Trainer(net.collect_params(), 'Adam', {
    'learning_rate': 0.1, 'wd': 4e-5})

epochs = 50
for epoch in range(epochs):
    total_train_loss = mx.nd.zeros(1, ctx=ctx)
    start = time.time()
    training_samples = 0
    for batch_idx, (data, label) in enumerate(train_data_loader):
        data = data.as_in_context(ctx)
        label = label.as_in_context(ctx)

        with autograd.record():
            output = net(data)
            loss = criterion(output, label)
        loss.backward()
        trainer.step(data.shape[0])
        total_train_loss += loss.sum()
        training_samples += data.shape[0]
        if batch_idx > 0 and batch_idx % 500 == 0:
            elapse = time.time() - start
            # uncomment this line will prevent this error to happen.
            # print(total_train_loss.asscalar()/training_samples)
            print('{}:[{}] samples/s in train'.format(batch_idx,
                                                      training_samples/elapse))

```

