4142,IssuesEvent,2016-10-22 16:06:31+00:00,6670942,boto/botocore,25672,eukaryote,327752,boto,opened,SigV4 Presigned URLs broken if URL contains blank query params,[],[],0,"Generating a sigv4 presigned URL when the base URL contains a query parameter without a value results in a presigned URL that doesn't contain the parameter at all, because parse_qs strips blank parameters by default. 

For example, 'https://s3.amazonaws.com/mybucket/mykey?uploads' is a base URL for creating a multipart upload URL, and the resulting presigned URL that is generated by the following code no longer has an 'uploads' param when SigV4 is used:

`
s3.generate_presigned_url(
    'create_multipart_upload',
    Params={
        'Bucket': 'mybucket',
        'Key': 'mykey',
    }
)
`



",{},{}
