4436,IssuesEvent,2016-10-25 00:28:37+00:00,54980593,pypa/setuptools,495018,dairiki,647025,pypa,opened,setup.py: incorrect dependency link ,[],[],0,"Setuptools’ setup.py adds a link for ``certifi`` to ``dependency_links``.  The link it adds (``https://pypi.python.org/packages/source/c/certifi/certifi-2016.9.26.tar.gz``) is broken (404.)

I'm not totally sure what's going on here.  My guess is that PyPI has changed how downloads are filed.  (Older packages seem to still be available under ``/packages/source``, but recently released packages appear not to be.)

In any case, this breaks buildout — at least for me.  Buildout picks up the broken dependency link from the setuptools egg and uses it (unsuccessfully) if an attempt is made to install ``certifi==2016.9.26``.",{},{}
