4671,IssuesEvent,2017-06-12 18:31:31+00:00,9252533,numenta/nupic,239726,scottpurdy,1039191,numenta,closed,SDRClassifierRegion does not play well with scalar value prediction,"[{'id': 119445174, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/numenta/nupic/labels/priority:3', 'name': 'priority:3', 'color': '009800', 'default': False}, {'id': 61249142, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/numenta/nupic/labels/subject:algorithms', 'name': 'subject:algorithms', 'color': 'c7def8', 'default': False}, {'id': 378158329, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/numenta/nupic/labels/triage', 'name': 'triage', 'color': 'BBBBBB', 'default': False}, {'id': 34780061, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/numenta/nupic/labels/type:bug', 'name': 'type:bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': False}]",[],3,"Discussed with Yuwei and we agreed that the SDRClassifierRegion inherited some problems from the CLAClassifierRegion and that it does not work with multistep scalar prediction.

<a href=""https://github.com/numenta/nupic/blob/master/src/nupic/regions/CLAClassifierRegion.py#L380""> This </a>  is the line we discussed that was inherited from the CLAClassifier that creates this problem. 

A related <a href=""https://github.com/numenta/nupic/issues/3078""> issue  </a> from someone experiencing the same problem I had.

@ywcui1990 what would be your proposal to making this region work both for traditional classification and scalar value prediction?

@rhyolight I am putting the prediction network api example on hold until this is resolved.
",{},{}
4679,IssuesEvent,2015-10-07 18:32:10+00:00,9252533,numenta/nupic,1100496,ppuskari,1039191,numenta,opened,"Ubuntu 14.04 LTS build fail after commit 623 on September 26, 2015",[],[],0,"> What did you do? (steps to reproduce)
Success compile and build of the full NuPic system  core and nupic  with the 623 commit on September 26, 2015

Update to any > commit version up to present and the build will fail with a a failure to locate the capnproto install path during the cmake step after building requirements
> What happened? (actual results)
Compilation and installation success with build 623 commit
Compilation failure during cmake process using any commit level after 623 on September 26, 2015

> What should have happened? (expected results)
Successful build
> Additional Information (operating system, python version, NuPIC commit SHA, etc.)
Will need to check what has changed in the cmakelists that causes the detection of an installed capnproto to not pass with these later builds.  It appears this was perhaps fixed in a previous bug fix however before this commit then maybe dropped somehow?",{},{}
