4747,IssuesEvent,2015-03-24 14:12:58+00:00,2665618,inveniosoftware/invenio,189798,jirikuncar,1157480,inveniosoftware,closed,WebSubmit: warn user when Javascript is disabled,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/c_WebSubmit', 'name': 'c_WebSubmit', 'color': 'ededed'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/p_minor', 'name': 'p_minor', 'color': 'f7c6c7'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/t_enhancement', 'name': 't_enhancement', 'color': 'eb6420'}]",[],1,"Originally on 2012-05-08

WebSubmit requires to have Javascript enabled on the browser client. While it is hoped that this requirement would be removed (see  [Savannah ticket 3178](https://savannah.cern.ch/task/index.php?3178)), it would be nice in the meantime to display a message to the user when visiting a submission page with Javascript disabled:

```
<noscript>
  Submissions requires to have Javascript enabled. 
  Please enable Javascript on your browser in order to submit.
</noscript>
```",{},{}
