5182,IssuesEvent,2017-12-14 16:39:29+00:00,3470471,FortAwesome/Font-Awesome,4849251,katie1348,1505683,FortAwesome,opened,fa-stack with fa-hexagon as background,[],[],0,"I have been using Font Awesome 5.0.1 Pro and using the Hexagon as a background.

When placing icons into a circle, they align as expected, centred in the circle. Code is as follows:

```css			
<span class=""fa-stack fa-2x"">
    <i class=""fas fa-circle fa-stack-2x"" style=""color: red;""></i>
    <i class=""fas fa-envelope fa-stack-1x fa-inverse""></i>
</span>
```
When I use the same code, but use a hexagon, I get an offset to the left, which creates a visual anomaly. 

```css
<span class=""fa-stack fa-2x"">
    <i class=""fas fa-hexagon fa-stack-2x"" style=""color: red;""></i>
    <i class=""fas fa-envelope fa-stack-1x fa-inverse""></i>
</span>
```
It does not seem to matter which icon is used, as the few I have tried all do the same thing.

It is reasonably simple to see this in a page, as the code above with reference to ""fontawesome-all.min.css"" was all I had.

You can see the effect in the image below.

![icons](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4849251/34003492-49773b9c-e0ed-11e7-930b-90fbe4c23d31.PNG)
",{},{}
