5602,IssuesEvent,2016-10-04 13:01:04+00:00,16316451,GoogleCloudPlatform/google-cloud-python,5008293,rishsriv,2810941,GoogleCloudPlatform,opened,'table.insert_data()' frequently fails in the Python BiqQuery client with error: [Errno 32] Broken pipe,[],[],0,"Streaming inserts to a BigQuery table frequently fail with `error: [Errno 32] Broken pipe` on Debian 7.11 with Python 2.7.3 and google-cloud-python 0.20. The error occurs around 30% of the time.

This happens with a small number of rows (<2000), where each row is less than 2kb. Hence, it is unlikely to be a quota problem.

Here is the code that leads to the problem:

```
from google.cloud import bigquery
client = bigquery.Client(project=PROJECT_NAME)
dataset = client.dataset(DATASET_NAME)
table = dataset.table(TABLE_NAME, schema=SCHEMA)

#some code to generate ROWS to be inserted

table.insert_data(ROWS)
```

Here is the full error traceback:

```
