> 4. Stacktrace if available

`completion_queue.poll()` hangs on [this line](https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/9c519434be0ee80fcf66b433fc8c053ce9ac383b/src/python/grpcio/grpc/_channel.py#L485)

> 5. Steps to reproduce

Run code sample - hangs in `topic.publish(...)`

> 6. Code example

```python
from concurrent.futures import ProcessPoolExecutor
from time import sleep
from google.cloud import pubsub

def start_publishing(task):
    client = pubsub.Client()
    topic = client.topic('my-topic')
    for i in range(5):
        print('task {}, publishing {}'.format(task, i))
        topic.publish('this is a test ' + str(i))
        print('task {}, published {}'.format(task, i))
        sleep(1)

def done(future):
    r,m = future.result()
    print(r)
    print(m)

if __name__ == '__main__':
    executor = ProcessPoolExecutor(max_workers=4)
    for t in range(4):
        future = executor.submit(start_publishing, t)
        future.add_done_callback(done)
```",{},{}
