5737,IssuesEvent,2017-10-16 18:29:27+00:00,4086616,shadowsocks/shadowsocks,16555852,shawondas,3006190,shadowsocks,opened,How to save the user data record? ,[],[],0,"I am using a shadowsocks server. I have made 3 ports on it. I can check every port data usges with 

sudo iptables -nvL -t filter --line-numbers

comment. But if I restart my server, everything cleared! How can I save those? that it will not lose these data? ",{},{}
5756,IssuesEvent,2016-05-18 18:09:52+00:00,7137821,cloudtools/troposphere,13950481,dsmithwfm,3028687,cloudtools,opened,Option mappings in templates for Troposphere like Pyplates.,[],[],0,"Hello,

I originally started out using Pyplates and it has an awesome feature.  That feature is a command line argument to specify an options mapping .yaml file.  This let me setup an Integration, QA, and Production environment.  The problem is the Pyplates Github repo seems dead and an issue on DependsOn statements I opened will probably never be looked at.  I'd rather not use a tool with little to no current development so, I'm abandoning the idea of Pyplates.

This leaves me wanting to use Troposphere to convert my CF to PY and then use cfn2py as needed.  I'd love to have a Python wrapper that allows specifying options mappings.  Is there something else I'm missing to quickly set this up or should I bite the bullet and try writing my own script to generate templates?",{},{}
