5798,IssuesEvent,2016-04-14 01:33:34+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,157586,jsirois,3065172,pantsbuild,closed,Setup-py task does not resolve symlinks,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/in-progress', 'name': 'in-progress', 'color': '009800'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/user%20reported', 'name': 'user reported', 'color': '5319e7'}]",[],3,"There seems to be a small mismatch in the behavior of `./pants setup-py` and `./pants binary` regarding the resolution of symbolic links.

Given the following code, where `.auroraversion` is pointing to an external file, the `binary` task resolves the symlink and packages the original file. 
```
python_library(
  name = 'auroraversion',
  resources = [ '.auroraversion' ]
)
```
However, the `setup-py` task is only packaging the symlink itself. This leads to an sdist with a dangling symlink which cannot be converted to a wheel.

Expected behavior would be that the `setup-py` task behaves `binary` here and include the original file.",{},{}
5811,IssuesEvent,2018-08-23 17:13:01+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,1305167,cosmicexplorer,3065172,pantsbuild,closed,deprecate -q as a recursive option,"[{'id': 407072147, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw0MDcwNzIxNDc=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/fix-it', 'name': 'fix-it', 'color': 'c5def5', 'default': False}, {'id': 783132700, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw3ODMxMzI3MDA=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/options', 'name': 'options', 'color': 'f4a47f', 'default': False}]",[],8,"Running a pants command as `./pants -q <args...>` suppresses all output, but putting `-q` after one of the goals causes pants to display other workunit output except for that goal (e.g. `./pants run -q <args...>`). This could be useful, but it seems far more likely to be confusing that `-q` is accepted as an argument, but doesn't actually quiet all the output, and for the case of `./pants run -q <args...>`, the user almost definitely wants to have only the output of running the executable, e.g. for consumption in a script. It might clarify things a bit to deprecate the recursive behavior.",{},{}
5818,IssuesEvent,2015-11-12 20:52:53+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,1273972,chrispesto,3065172,pantsbuild,closed,"Implement ""npm test""",[],[],1,"Now that https://github.com/pantsbuild/pants/pull/2168 is in master and Pants is preserving scripts from package.json files, it can run ""npm test"" (which is really just a shorthand for ""npm run test""). Once https://github.com/pantsbuild/pants/issues/2330 is done, build on that functionality to implement test running. Pants should report back the test results as with other languages.",{},{}
