5839,IssuesEvent,2017-05-09 00:17:24+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,46740,stuhood,3065172,pantsbuild,opened,Collection of resources not transitive,"[{'id': 22426646, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': True}, {'id': 407699339, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/jvm', 'name': 'jvm', 'color': '0052cc', 'default': False}]",[],0,"The `resources` arg on JVM and Python targets is now deprecated, but the behaviour of only collecting directly declared resources remains.

The result for the JVM is that resources are only collected transitively in the graph if they are directly depended on by a JvmTarget.

While this behaviour has existed for a while, it was difficult to run into it when resources were directly declared as ""owned"" by some particular target.",{},{}
5843,IssuesEvent,2018-08-25 16:05:57+00:00,15381974,groveco/django-sql-explorer,693700,chrisclark,3093407,groveco,closed,Time for a new release?,[],[],16,"Hey, great work on this tool!

