5878,IssuesEvent,2018-04-21 22:09:39+00:00,70530854,awslabs/serverless-application-model,1444420,jlhood,3299148,awslabs,opened,Cannot use Fn::Sub to reference RestApiId in Function Events definition,[],[],0,"**Description:**

When defining a RestApi as an Event source for an AWS::Serverless::Function, you can specify a RestApiId. SAM translator supports specifying that id as a hardcoded value or using !Ref. However, it doesn't support using !Sub:

https://github.com/awslabs/serverless-application-model/blob/9ca6e340f051eaa670962303aff64f6cbeea181e/samtranslator/plugins/api/implicit_api_plugin.py#L158-L165

**Steps to reproduce the issue:**

Define a serverless function and serverless api in your template SAM template. Add an event mapping to the serverless function, but use !Sub to reference the api resource like this:

```
Resources:
  MyFunction:
    Type: AWS::Serverless::Function
    Properties:
      ...
      Events:
        RestApi:
          Type: Api
          Properties:
            RestApiId: !Sub ${MyRestApi} # doesn't work when !Ref MyRestApi does
```

Then try to create a changeset with the template and SAM will error with:



**Observed result:**

ChangeSet ends up in FAILED state with message `RestApiId must be a valid reference to an 'AWS::Serverless::Api' resource`

**Expected result:**

ChangeSet should be created successfully",{},{}
5913,IssuesEvent,2018-03-12 21:23:48+00:00,9861437,imageio/imageio,3015475,almarklein,3678179,imageio,closed,`if imageio.get_reader(...): pass` fails for FfmpegFormat.Reader objects,"[{'id': 143381939, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/imageio/imageio/labels/core', 'name': 'core', 'color': '207de5', 'default': False}, {'id': 38460459, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/imageio/imageio/labels/type:%20bug', 'name': 'type: bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': False}]",[],2,"The following statement:

`if imageio.get_reader('<video0>'): pass`

raises 'OverflowError: cannot convert float infinity to integer' (at least in Python 2.7)

It seems that `FfmpegFormat.Reader` has no `__nonzero__()` method (nor `__bool__()` for Python 3?), so the `__len__()` method is evaluated, which, in this case, returns `float('inf')`.

A quick hack for anyone running into this issue could be to use `if ... is not None`.
(see [stackoverflow](https://stackoverflow.com/a/7816439/4720018))

",{},{}
