6286,IssuesEvent,2018-05-27 19:48:02+00:00,91356408,allenai/allennlp,3291951,matt-gardner,5667695,allenai,closed,Make Attention and MatrixAttention more memory efficient,"[{'id': 757402569, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/allenai/allennlp/labels/P3', 'name': 'P3', 'color': '1262a8', 'default': False}]",[],6,"The way I originally implemented the `Attention` module lets you swap out `SimilarityFunctions` to try a bunch of options if you want, but it does so at the expense of memory usage, often using _way_ more memory than is necessary.  It'd be better to just have `Attention` be an abstract, `Registrable` `Module`, with concrete implementations matching our `SimilarityFunctions`, but more memory efficient.  You'd still get the modularity, but without sacrificing memory usage.  #346 has one instance of this for `MatrixAttention`.

Next time I'm working on a model where this is the bottleneck, I'll just fix it, but I don't know when that will be.  If someone wants to contribute modules that do this, that'd be great.",{},{}
