6905,IssuesEvent,2015-03-26 05:53:08+00:00,23984796,jupyter/nbgrader,83444,jhamrick,7388996,jupyter,closed,Cleanup the nbgrader pipeline,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/jupyter/nbgrader/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/jupyter/nbgrader/labels/important', 'name': 'important', 'color': 'f7c6c7'}]",[],0,"As decided in the dev meeting, there should be a strict pipeline between the various grading steps. Each app will assume there are input files that fit the path ""<?name>/<?student>/<?problem_set>/<?notebook>"", where ""name"" is a name corresponding to one of the workflow steps (e.g. ""submitted"", ""autograded"", ""feedback"") and that the output files will follow the same format. This path will be configurable (as well as the names of the workflow steps), but will be the same across all the subapps. Additionally, each of the variables that match the different parts of the path can be filtered by, which allows filtering by student, problem set, and/or notebook, as the instructor desires.

This will require making some changes to nbconvert (breaking apart the main convert_notebooks function to be more easy to override).

![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/83444/6654319/68a60ec8-ca78-11e4-9561-d040589a5621.png)
",{},{}
