7126,IssuesEvent,2017-09-28 10:07:45+00:00,98336690,deepmind/pysc2,23448360,DengpanFu,8596759,deepmind,opened,some questions about replay,[],[],0,"I tried to complete supervised learning from the replays, so i parsed the replay to get feature_layers, available actions, exactly executed actions for every time-step. the core code i used:
```
# controller is the replay game controller
feature = features.Fetures(controller.game_info())
while True:
    controller.step(step_mul)
    obs = controller.observe()
    if obs.player_result:
        break
    available_actions = feature.available_actions(obs.observation)
    exec_actions = []
    for ac in obs.actions:
      try:
        exec_act = feature.reverse_action(ac)
      except ValueError:
        exec_act = features.actions.FunctionCall(0, [])  # no_op
      exec_actions.append(exec_act)
```
Then i found something strange. i print every time-step's action, the following are two of them:
```
Available actios: [0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 9, 335, 336, 451, 343, 344, 452]
Execute actions: [FunctionCall(function=1, arguments=[[11, 43]])]
...
Available actions: [0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 168, 335, 336, 451, 452]
Execute actions: [FunctionCall(function=2, arguments=[[1], [43, 24]]), FunctionCall(function=9, arguments=[]), FunctionCall(function=467, arguments=[[0]])]
...
Available actios: [0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 453, 12, 331, 332, 333, 334, 13, 274, 451, 452]
Execute actions: [FunctionCall(function=451, arguments=[[0], [49, 7]]), FunctionCall(function=451, arguments=[[0], [47, 7]])]
```
I have the following questions:
1. In a time-step, more than one action were actually made and send to the SC2 server(step_mul was set to 1, i got these actions frame by frame), does that means the player played fast and produced more than one action in a very short time and we should predict multi-actions at a times-step ?
2. The second shows that, the actually taken action may be out of the available actions' range, does that means the player could carry out some invalid actions(while the SC2 server will ignore these actions) ?
3. The third shows that, an action can be performed multi-times with different arguments in the same time-step, that's odd, and how can we know which coordinates to predict ?
 
Any suggestion is appreciate. @tewalds


",{},{}
