7634,IssuesEvent,2017-06-02 05:12:38+00:00,39940111,lyst/lightfm,13383608,chrisbangun,10947873,lyst,opened,AssertionError after split dataset to train and test,[],[],0,"Hi, I've spent quite some time in exploring LightFM and currently stuck on several things. Could you please look at my issue and lend me your help to resolve it?

1. How do we split our training and testing data? so far, I did it using `sklearn train_test_split` method? in recommender system problem, can we really do it like this?
`train, test = train_test_split(prebooking, test_size = 0.2, random_state=42)`

2. what are the best data representation that we need to create in order to make the most out of LightFM? For instance, I have the following data:
![screenshot from 2017-06-02 12-10-54](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/13383608/26711708/8eabd484-478c-11e7-92df-6ceb80a2eb13.png)


Having seen the code provided in the examples, I tried to do this:
```
def build_interaction_matrix(df, row_name, col_name, user_id_mapping, item_id_mapping):
    """"""
    given raw dataframe
    """"""
    n_rows = len(user_id_mapping)
    n_cols = len(item_id_mapping)
    mat = sp.lil_matrix((n_rows, n_cols), dtype=np.float64)
    for idx, row in df.iterrows():
        _rid, _cid =  user_id_mapping.get(row[row_name]), item_id_mapping.get(row[col_name])
        if row['interaction'] > 3:
            mat[_rid, _cid] = 1.0
        else:
            mat[_rid, _cid] = -1.0
    return mat.tocoo()

# Mapping cookie_id and hotel_id from train data to zero-based index
rid_to_idx_train, idx_to_rid_train,\
        cid_to_idx_train, idx_to_cid_train = get_df_matrix_mappings(train,
                                                        'cookie_id',
                                                        'hotel_id')
    
train_matrix = build_interaction_matrix(train, 'cookie_id', 'hotel_id', rid_to_idx_train, cid_to_idx_train)

# Mapping cookie_id and hotel_id from test data to zero-based index
rid_to_idx_test, idx_to_rid_test,\
        cid_to_idx_test, idx_to_cid_test = get_df_matrix_mappings(test,
                                                        'cookie_id',
                                                        'hotel_id')
    
test_matrix = build_interaction_matrix(test, 'cookie_id', 'hotel_id', rid_to_idx_test, cid_to_idx_test)
```
From the code above, I got two sparse matrix - train_matrix and test_matrix. Each has shape
```
train_matrix.shape: (1025081, 9282)
test_matrix.shape: ((450553, 8288)
```

Then I tried to feed it to the lightFM model:
```
model = LightFM(learning_rate=0.05,
                loss='warp',
                item_alpha=1e-6,
                no_components=30)
model.fit(train_matrix, epochs=500, num_threads=16)
```

Unfortunately, I got an error when executing this code:
```
train_precision = precision_at_k(model, train, k=10, num_threads=12).mean()
test_precision = precision_at_k(model, test, k=10, num_threads=12).mean()
train_auc = auc_score(model, train).mean()
test_auc = auc_score(model, test).mean()
print('Precision: train %.2f, test %.2f.' % (train_precision, test_precision))
print('AUC: train %.2f, test %.2f.' % (train_auc, test_auc))
```

the error is:
