# trailing slash added here?
pprint(products_endpoint.get())

```

In any case, this library refuses to play nice with [flask_restless](https://github.com/jfinkels/flask-restless), which IMO is a show-stopper.

This code works perfectly fine in testing the GET part of the API:
```
products_url = 'http://localhost:5000/api/v1/products'
headers = {
    'Content-Type': 'application/json',
    'Accept': 'application/vnd.api+json'
}

response = requests.get(products_url, headers=headers)
assert response.status_code == 200
pprint(response.json())
```

Proof the manager log:
```
127.0.0.1 - - [31/Mar/2017 13:57:49] ""GET /api/v1/products HTTP/1.1"" 200 -
```

Any idea why the same exact url hit from this library would return a different status code/results?",{},{}
