7872,IssuesEvent,2016-08-16 16:14:51+00:00,40328394,angr/angr,759365,axt,12520807,angr,opened,Question about simrun and USE_SIMPLIFIED_CCALLS,[],[],0,"I'm running the following test code:
```python
#!/usr/bin/python
import logging

import io
import angr
import claripy
from simuvex import o

if __name__ == ""__main__"":
    code = b""\x66\x83\xfe\x7f\x7f\x17""
    proj = angr.Project(io.BytesIO(code), load_options={'main_opts': {'custom_arch':'x86'}})
    block = proj.factory.block(0x0)
    block.pp()
    print """"
    block.vex.pp()
    print """"
    state = proj.factory.blank_state(addr=0x0, add_options={o.USE_SIMPLIFIED_CCALLS})
    simrun  = proj.factory.sim_run(state)
    exitguard = simrun.conditional_exits[0].se.constraints[0]

    print ""Default exit          : "", simrun.default_exit.regs.eip
    print ""Default exit guard    : "", simrun.default_exit_guard
    print ""Conditional exit      : "", simrun.conditional_exits[0].regs.eip
    print ""Conditional exit guard: "", simrun.conditional_exits[0].se.constraints[0]

```

This is the results it gerates:
```
0x0:	cmp	si, 0x7f
0x4:	jg	0x1d

IRSB {
   t0:Ity_I16 t1:Ity_I16 t2:Ity_I16 t3:Ity_I32 t4:Ity_I32 t5:Ity_I1 t6:Ity_I32 t7:Ity_I32 t8:Ity_I32 t9:Ity_I32 t10:Ity_I32 t11:Ity_I32

   00 | ------ IMark(0x0, 4, 0) ------
   01 | t2 = GET:I16(esi)
   02 | PUT(cc_op) = 0x00000005
   03 | t3 = 16Uto32(t2)
   04 | PUT(cc_dep1) = t3
   05 | PUT(cc_dep2) = 0x0000007f
   06 | PUT(cc_ndep) = 0x00000000
   07 | PUT(eip) = 0x00000004
   08 | ------ IMark(0x4, 2, 0) ------
   09 | t10 = x86g_calculate_condition(0x0000000e,0x00000005,t3,0x0000007f,0x00000000):Ity_I32
   10 | t5 = 32to1(t10)
   11 | if (t5) { PUT(eip) = 0x6; Ijk_Boring }
   NEXT: PUT(eip) = 0x0000001d; Ijk_Boring
}

Default exit          :  <BV32 0x1d>
Default exit guard    :  <Bool (0#16 .. reg_20_0_16) > 0x7f>
Conditional exit      :  <BV32 0x6>
Conditional exit guard:  <Bool (0#16 .. reg_20_0_16) <= 0x7f>
```

My questions:
- maybe I understand the concepts wrong, but shouldn't be `0x6` the default exit, and `0x1d` the conditional exit?
- instead of ZeroExtend + unsigned comparison, shouldn't be there a SignExtend + signed comparison?

Thanks.
