| Camera Model | SR300 & ZR300 |
| Firmware Version |   | 
| Operating System & Version | Ubuntu 16.04.03 LTS  | 
| Kernel Version (Linux Only)  | 4.4.0-98-generic  | 

Hi everyone,

I bought the elements of a development kit like this one : https://up-shop.org/home/117-up-zr300-realsense-camera-robotic-developement-kit.html
The only difference is that my UP board has 2GB RAM & 16 Gb eMMC.

I've installed Ubuntu following those steps : https://01.org/developerjourney/recipe/intel-realsense-robotic-development-kit#introduction
I'm trying to setup everything to work with the SR300 or ZR300 on the USB 3.0 OTG port available on my board as the steps should be the same for setting up the system even if the mentionned camera is a R200 in this tutorial.
I've tried to install the upboard headers as mentionned but the kernel patch is not applied fully if these headers are installed instead of the generic ones.

After following those steps I've followed the ones on this github installation page for the ZR300 : https://github.com/IntelRealSense/librealsense/blob/v1.12.1/doc/installation.md
And the steps described in the new version of the SDK for the SR300 : https://github.com/IntelRealSense/librealsense

 I successfully applied the patch to the generic headers and the device seems to be detected as the `dmesg` command shows : 
* For SR300 :
```
[ 5680.371803] usb 1-1: new high-speed USB device number 18 using xhci_hcd
[ 5680.501708] usb 1-1: New USB device found, idVendor=05e3, idProduct=0610
[ 5680.501734] usb 1-1: New USB device strings: Mfr=1, Product=2, SerialNumber=0
[ 5680.501753] usb 1-1: Product: USB2.0 Hub
