8220,IssuesEvent,2016-01-23 04:21:58+00:00,43056951,graphql-python/graphene,188257,syrusakbary,15002022,graphql-python,closed,Graphene as a validation library,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/graphql-python/graphene/labels/question', 'name': 'question', 'color': 'cc317c'}]",[],2,"This is probably not the best place to discuss this as it is not a bug report, but I was wondering how we should approach data validation with graphql and graphene, especially with its Django integration.

For example, should graphene replace the django forms layer as well? I believe it should and it can, since its validation capabilities are much richer. It is possible to validate if something is a string in django, but going beyond that, for example, ensuring a value is a list of strings is not possible without custom code.

We should discuss and document the best practices here.

I see graphene as ultimately replacing the urls, views and forms parts of django. ",{},{}
