8812,IssuesEvent,2017-02-21 10:42:51+00:00,1360247,django-polymorphic/django-polymorphic,138215,adamcharnock,19997027,django-polymorphic,opened,Only base classes provided in Django 1.11b1,[],[],0,"I'm testing a project against Django 1.11b1 and it seems that only the base model is being returned in the resulting ``PolymorphicQuerySet``. Only upon calling ``get_real_instances()`` to I get the actual model instances.

Here is my working:

```python
>>> Action.objects.all()
# 'Action' is the base class
<PolymorphicQuerySet [<Action: Action object>, <Action: Action object>, <Action: Action object>, <Action: Action object>]>
>>> Action.objects.all().get_real_instances()
# Now the resolution works
[<EmailAction: Email toby@example.com>, <EmailAction: Email adam@example.com>, <EmailAction: Email foo@example.com>, <EmailAction: Email bar@example.com>]
```

This seemed to work just fine when testing against Django 1.10.",{},{}
8815,IssuesEvent,2017-02-26 16:14:11+00:00,24161806,explosion/cymem,22738317,mratsim,20011530,explosion,opened,Building fails on non-UTF8 terminals,[],[],0,"I was building cymem from source through an SSH connection and it fails due to an unicode character in README.rst

```python
Traceback (most recent call last):
