9285,IssuesEvent,2018-05-12 19:48:55+00:00,87939708,flask-dashboard/Flask-MonitoringDashboard,17162650,FlyingBird95,31957504,flask-dashboard,closed,Overview table: saving sorting criterion / or make decreasing order of hits default,[],[],1,"1. Saving sorting criterion would be really nice to have.

2. Alternatively, simpler, and anyway better than what we have now is making the default ordering 'decreasing number of hits'. 

Personally I find myself always sorting in decreasing order of overall number of hits. I care about the most used API endpoints first. 

-- 

In any case, anything is better than alphabetical: alphabetical is good for telephone books, not for software systems. I've even wrote an entire paper about this once :) 

https://www.researchgate.net/publication/288448275_Overthrowing_the_Tyranny_of_Alphabetical_Ordering_in_Documentation_Systems



",{},{}
9305,IssuesEvent,2018-04-18 11:12:16+00:00,61185770,cldf/pycldf,870184,xrotwang,33516590,cldf,opened,VALIDATORS must be a list of triples,[],"[{'login': 'xrotwang', 'id': 870184, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/870184?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/xrotwang', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/xrotwang', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/xrotwang/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/xrotwang/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/xrotwang/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/xrotwang/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/xrotwang/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/xrotwang/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/xrotwang/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/xrotwang/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/xrotwang/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"`validators.VALIDATORS` - the registry of validators - must be changed from the current `dict` to a `list` of triples (table, col, validator) - where
- `table` specifies a table - either by term URI or by file name; `None` can be used to specify validators that apply to all tables
- `col` specifies a column - either by term URI or by column name
- `validator` is the callable implementing the check.

This will make it much simpler to plug custom validation code into the `validate` method.",{},{}
